
EARTHQUAKE PREDICTION SYSTEM
===========================

A full-stack earthquake prediction prototype using LSTM (Deep Learning)
with a React frontend and Flask backend.

--------------------------------------------------
TECH STACK
--------------------------------------------------

Frontend:
- React.js
- Axios
- SCSS

Backend:
- Flask
- Flask-CORS
- TensorFlow (LSTM)
- NumPy
- Pandas
- Scikit-learn
- Joblib

--------------------------------------------------
PROJECT STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------

earthquake-prediction/
|
|-- backend/
|   |-- app.py
|   |-- model.py
|   |-- database.csv
|   |-- requirements.txt
|   |-- lstm_model.keras
|   |-- scaler.pkl
|
|-- frontend/
|   |-- src/
|   |-- package.json
|
|-- README.txt

--------------------------------------------------
BACKEND SETUP
--------------------------------------------------

1. Move to backend directory
   cd backend

2. Create virtual environment
   python -m venv venv

3. Activate virtual environment

   Windows:
   venv\Scripts\activate

   Mac/Linux:
   source venv/bin/activate

4. Install dependencies
   pip install -r requirements.txt

   If TensorFlow fails on Windows:
   pip install tensorflow-cpu

--------------------------------------------------
TRAIN THE MODEL
--------------------------------------------------

Run:
python model.py

Enter:
- Latitude
- Longitude
- Depth

This generates:
- lstm_model.keras
- scaler.pkl

--------------------------------------------------
RUN FLASK SERVER
--------------------------------------------------

python app.py

Server runs on:
http://localhost:5000

--------------------------------------------------
FRONTEND SETUP
--------------------------------------------------

1. Move to frontend directory
   cd frontend

2. Install dependencies
   npm install

3. Create .env file in frontend folder

   REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:5000

4. Start frontend
   npm start

Frontend runs on:
http://localhost:3000

--------------------------------------------------
API DETAILS
--------------------------------------------------

POST /predict

Request JSON:
{
  "latitude": 28.6,
  "longitude": 77.2,
  "depth": 10,
  "date": "2025-01-01"
}

--------------------------------------------------
DISCLAIMER
--------------------------------------------------

This project is for educational and research purposes only.
It is NOT a real-world earthquake warning system.
